Equipment program (in proc. 2009/54129-9), which aims at the acquisition of equipment for research that are not usually acquired at regular grantsdue to their high cost. Learn about our<strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=349&amp;lang=en\">mission, vision and values.</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThe LaCTAD is being created at UNICAMP in combination with the areas of <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=26&amp;lang=en\">Cell Biology</a></strong>, <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=28&amp;lang=en\">Genomics</a></strong>, <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=33&amp;lang=en\">Proteomics</a></strong>and <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=30&amp;lang=en\">Bioinformatics</a></strong>, in order to develop advanced studies by using the state of the art equipment and Techniques.\r\n\r\nThe installation of this Laboratory is based on the acquisition of scientific equipment to be continuously used and operated by a specialized team (<strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=20&amp;lang=en\">learn about our team</a></strong>) enabling a better use of each device beyond offer high quality and cost-benefit services to the community of the State University of Campinas (UNICAMP) and other Universities and Research Institutes.\r\n\r\n<strong>For estimate or Request our Services, you must fill out the form by <a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=52&amp;lang=en\">clicking here.</a></strong>'),(61,39,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(62,5,'english-title','What is LaCTAD?'),(63,5,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(64,5,'english-content','The Central Laboratory of High Performance Technologies (LaCTAD) is an initiative of UNICAMP supported by FAPESP, through the Multi-User Equipment program (in proc. 2009/54129-9), which aims at the acquisition of equipment for research that are not usually acquired at regular grantsdue to their high cost. Learn about our<strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=349&amp;lang=en\">mission, vision and values.</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThe LaCTAD is being created at UNICAMP in combination with the areas of <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=26&amp;lang=en\">Cell Biology</a></strong>, <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=28&amp;lang=en\">Genomics</a></strong>, <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=33&amp;lang=en\">Proteomics</a></strong>and <strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=30&amp;lang=en\">Bioinformatics</a></strong>, in order to develop advanced studies by using the state of the art equipment and Techniques.\r\n\r\nThe installation of this Laboratory is based on the acquisition of scientific equipment to be continuously used and operated by a specialized team (<strong><a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=20&amp;lang=en\">learn about our team</a></strong>) enabling a better use of each device beyond offer high quality and cost-benefit services to the community of the State University of Campinas (UNICAMP) and other Universities and Research Institutes.\r\n\r\n<strong>For estimate or Request our Services, you must fill out the form by <a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=52&amp;lang=en\">clicking here.</a></strong>'),(65,5,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(82,26,'english-title','Flow Cytometry'),(83,26,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(84,26,'english-content','Flow cytometry is a quick and accurate technology that measures and analyzes separately  the optical properties of a large number of cells or particles, such as cells, bacteria, beads, yeasts, platelets, nuclei and other types of particles of size between 0.2 to 50μm, in samples such as peripheral blood, bone marrow, cerebrospinal fluid, pleural fluid, peritoneal, or even solid tissues prepared in suspension, such as spleen, lymph nodes and tumor masses. It is necessary for the samples to be tested are suspended.\r\n\r\nThe samples will be analyzed by immunofluorescence labeling with different fluorochromes, which are excited by the specific laser of the equipment.\r\n\r\nThe use of fluorochromes with different fluorescence characteristics, several lasers and several photodetectors allows the flow cytometers to measure many features simultaneously of each particle as cell diameter, granular structures within the cells and fluorescence intensity.\r\n\r\nTherefore, Flow Cytometry have numerous applications, we describe below some:\r\n\r\n- Identification of cell populations and subpopulations and their constituents\r\n\r\n- Proliferation Cell\r\n\r\n- RedOx\r\n\r\n- Apoptosis\r\n\r\n- Cell Cycle\r\n\r\n- Immunofenotyping\r\n\r\n- Gene expression\r\n\r\nOther techniques of Flow Cytometry can be implemented.\r\n\r\nFor the analysis, will be available computers with software that users can do their own analyzes.\r\n\r\nLinks of free software of analysis result of Flow Cytometry:\r\n\r\n- Flowing: <a href=\"http://www.flowingsoftware.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.flowingsoftware.com</a>\r\n\r\n- FCS Filter: <a href=\"http://www.softflow.com/Frame.php?Page=FCSFilter&amp;SubPage=/Downloads\">http://www.softflow.com/Frame.php?Page=FCSFilter&amp;SubPage=/Downloads</a>\r\n\r\n- WinMDI:<a href=\"http://www.cyto.purdue.edu/flowcyt/software/Winmdi.htm\"> http://www.cyto.purdue.edu/flowcyt/software/Winmdi.htm</a>\r\n\r\n- Cyflogic:<a href=\"http://www.cyflogic.com/\"> http://www.cyflogic.com/</a>'),(85,26,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(89,16,'english-title','IX Bioinformatics course'),(90,16,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(91,16,'english-content','English description here!'),(92,16,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(107,47,'_edit_last','1'),(108,47,'_edit_lock','1435772720:1'),(109,47,'english-title','Next Generation Sequencing'),(110,47,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(111,47,'english-content','We currently work with the Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencing platform, which offer the following sequencing options:\r\n\r\nDNA:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Whole genome resequencing: small and large genomes</li>\r\n	<li>“De novo” sequencing: small and large genomes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDNA library options: single-read or paired-end fragments (&lt;1 kb); mate-pair (2-20 kb) libraries\r\nSequencing possibilities: up to 2 x 100 bp reads\r\n\r\nRNA:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transcriptome sequencing  (RNA-seq)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRNA library options: single-read or paired-end fragments (120-500bp)\r\nSequencing possibilities: up to 2 x 100 bp reads'),(112,47,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(113,49,'_edit_last','1'),(114,49,'field_5525a1ee20e9e','a:11:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_5525a1ee20e9e\";s:5:\"label\";s:10:\"Event Date\";s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"event_date\";s:4:\"type\";s:11:\"date_picker\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"date_format\";s:8:\"yy-mm-dd\";s:14:\"display_format\";s:8:\"dd/mm/yy\";s:9:\"first_day\";s:1:\"1\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(116,49,'position','acf_after_title'),(117,49,'layout','no_box'),(118,49,'hide_on_screen',''),(119,49,'_edit_lock','1435172164:1'),(120,16,'event_date','2015-07-20'),(121,16,'_event_date','field_5525a1ee20e9e'),(123,50,'_edit_last','1'),(124,50,'_edit_lock','1435772742:1'),(125,50,'english-title','Chain Termination Sequencing by Capillary Electrophoresis'),(126,50,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(127,50,'english-content','The “Sanger  sequencing” services are performed on the Applied Biosystems 3730xL sequencing platform, which offers the  following applications:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BAC-end sequencing</li>\r\n	<li>Validation of genetic constructs</li>\r\n	<li>“De novo” sequencing</li>\r\n	<li>Organelle genome sequencing</li>\r\n	<li>Re-sequencing (comparative genomics and indels)</li>\r\n	<li>Validation of PCR products</li>\r\n	<li>Others: on request. Please contact the LaCTAD.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Instructions for samples and primers preparation prior to sequencing:</strong>\r\n\r\nIn order to ensure adequate sequencing results, we strongly recommended that all the samples and primers should be diluted in ultrapure water or 10mM Tris-Cl buffer, pH 8.5 (Never add EDTA!). The presence of any other components in the sample solution could lead to poor sequencing results.\r\n\r\nThe quantity and volume of the samples to be sequenced must follow specific requirements, according to the following table:\r\n\r\n<dl><dd>\r\n<table border=\"1\" width=\"415\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"7\"><colgroup> <col width=\"191\" /> <col width=\"90\" /> <col width=\"90\" /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">Type</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\">Mass</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\">Volume</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">PCR product</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"></td>\r\n<td rowspan=\"10\" width=\"90\">The exact volume should be of 5uL in ultrapure water or 10mM Tris-Cl buffer, pH 8.5.\r\nNever add EDTA!</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\"><em>100-200 pb</em></td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>1-3 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\"><em>200-500 pb</em></td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>3-10 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\"><em>500-1000 pb</em></td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>5-20 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\"><em>1000-2000 pb</em></td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>10-40 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\"><em>&gt; 2000 pb</em></td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>20-50 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">Single-stranded (DNAss) plasmids</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>25-50 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">Double-stranded  (DNAds) plasmids</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>150-300 ng</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">Cosmid, BAC</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>0,5-1 ug</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"191\">Bacterial genomic DNA</td>\r\n<td width=\"90\"><em>2-3 ug</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</dd></dl>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Add 1ul of primer (3.2pmol) to 5uL of DNA, following the instructions bellow.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE</strong>: It is recommended  to use 3.2 pmol of primer in each reaction, diluted in a volume of 1ul of ultrapure water or 10mM Tris-Cl buffer, pH 8.5 ( never add EDTA!). Therefore, the DNA sample plus its corresponding primer will have a final volume of 6 ul.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMore details on the sample preparation prior to sequencing could be found at “<a href=\"http://www.ibt.lt/sc/files/BDTv3.1_Protocol_04337035.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Full Description of Genomic Services</a>”'),(128,50,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(133,52,'_edit_last','1'),(134,52,'english-title','HiSeq 2000 sequencing system (Illumina)'),(135,52,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(136,52,'english-content','The HiSeq 2000 system enables the elucidation of large and complex sequencing projects, due to its ability to process large numbers of samples and to generate a large data output for bioinformatics analysis of genomes and exomes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(137,52,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(138,52,'_edit_lock','1433874626:1'),(139,53,'_edit_last','1'),(140,53,'_edit_lock','1431541477:1'),(141,53,'english-title','Sequencer 3730XL DNA Analyzer (Applied Biosystems)'),(142,53,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(143,53,'english-content','The sequencing technology of the 3730xL DNA Analyzer ABI sequencer is based on the chain termination method (“ Sanger method”) combined with capillary electrophoresis. It is able to generate high-quality sequences with up to 1 kb in size. The system is equipped with 96 capillaries of 50cm in length and it can simultaneously hold up to ten 96-well plates in their feed compartment. There are three possible run modules (Fast, Long and XL-extended) which differ on running time and yield. For capillary electrophoresis, the system utilizes the POP-7 polymer. The optics system consists of a CCD camera along with several filters.'),(144,53,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(145,54,'_edit_last','1'),(148,54,'position','normal'),(149,54,'layout','no_box'),(150,54,'hide_on_screen','a:10:{i:0;s:7:\"excerpt\";i:1;s:13:\"custom_fields\";i:2;s:10:\"discussion\";i:3;s:8:\"comments\";i:4;s:9:\"revisions\";i:5;s:6:\"author\";i:6;s:6:\"format\";i:7;s:14:\"featured_image\";i:8;s:4:\"tags\";i:9;s:15:\"send-trackbacks\";}'),(151,54,'_edit_lock','1429121921:1'),(160,54,'field_552c330c4622f','a:14:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_552c330c4622f\";s:5:\"label\";s:7:\"Section\";s:4:\"name\";s:7:\"section\";s:4:\"type\";s:12:\"relationship\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"return_format\";s:6:\"object\";s:9:\"post_type\";a:4:{i:0;s:6:\"events\";i:1;s:8:\"services\";i:2;s:10:\"equipments\";i:3;s:7:\"members\";}s:8:\"taxonomy\";a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"all\";}s:7:\"filters\";a:1:{i:0;s:6:\"search\";}s:15:\"result_elements\";a:1:{i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";}s:3:\"max\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(182,70,'_edit_last','1'),(183,70,'question','Que tipos de amostras podem ser testadas no Citômetro de Fluxo?'),(184,70,'_question','field_552c31f356f07'),(185,70,'answer','Qualquer célula única ou suspensão de partículas podem ser analisadas​​, que incluem células de mamíferos, bactérias, fungos, tecido dissociado e esferas de poliestireno. Se suas células ou partículas em suspensão não estão isoladas, não se pode utilizar a Citometria de Fluxo.'),(186,70,'_answer','field_552c309c44a59'),(187,70,'english_question','What types of samples can be tested in the flow cytometer?'),(188,70,'_english_question','field_552c342513293'),(189,70,'english_answer','Any single cell or particle suspension can be analyzed, including mammalian cells, bacteria, fungi, dissociated tissue and polystyrene beads. If its cells or particles in suspension are not isolated, they cannot be used in Flow Cytometry.'),(190,70,'_english_answer','field_552c344913294'),(191,70,'section','a:1:{i:0;s:2:\"26\";}'),(192,70,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(193,70,'_edit_lock','1433966423:1'),(194,72,'_edit_last','1'),(195,72,'field_552c4244e25d3','a:11:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_552c4244e25d3\";s:5:\"label\";s:5:\"Photo\";s:4:\"name\";s:5:\"photo\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:11:\"save_format\";s:6:\"object\";s:12:\"preview_size\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:7:\"library\";s:3:\"all\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:2;}'),(197,72,'position','normal'),(198,72,'layout','no_box'),(199,72,'hide_on_screen','a:10:{i:0;s:7:\"excerpt\";i:1;s:13:\"custom_fields\";i:2;s:10:\"discussion\";i:3;s:8:\"comments\";i:4;s:9:\"revisions\";i:5;s:6:\"author\";i:6;s:6:\"format\";i:7;s:14:\"featured_image\";i:8;s:4:\"tags\";i:9;s:15:\"send-trackbacks\";}'),(200,72,'_edit_lock','1433190302:1'),(204,72,'field_552c4456114b7','a:14:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_552c4456114b7\";s:5:\"label\";s:6:\"Lattes\";s:4:\"name\";s:6:\"lattes\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:31:\"Type your lattes curriculum url\";s:7:\"prepend\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"append\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:4:\"html\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:3;}'),(205,72,'field_552c44ff114b9','a:14:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_552c44ff114b9\";s:5:\"label\";s:8:\"Linkedin\";s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"linkedin\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:32:\"Type your linkedin\'s profile url\";s:7:\"prepend\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"append\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:4:\"html\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:4;}'),(211,76,'_edit_last','1'),(212,76,'name','Member 1'),(213,76,'_name','field_552c42c6114b6'),(214,76,'photo','77'),(215,76,'_photo','field_552c4244e25d3'),(216,76,'bio','Lorem Ipsum é simplesmente uma simulação de texto da indústria tipográfica e de impressos, e vem sendo utilizado desde o século XVI, quando um impressor desconhecido pegou uma bandeja de tipos e os embaralhou para fazer um livro de modelos de tipos. Lorem Ipsum sobreviveu não só a cinco séculos, como também ao salto para a editoração eletrônica, permanecendo essencialmente inalterado. Se popularizou na década de 60, quando a Letraset lançou decalques contendo passagens de Lorem Ipsum, e mais recentemente quando passou a ser integrado a softwares de editoração eletrônica como Aldus PageMaker.'),(217,76,'_bio','field_552c44e7114b8'),(218,76,'email','lalala@hotmail.com'),(219,76,'_email','field_552c4588114ba'),(220,76,'lattes',''),(221,76,'_lattes','field_552c4456114b7'),(222,76,'linkedin',''),(223,76,'_linkedin','field_552c44ff114b9'),(224,76,'_edit_lock','1428965070:1'),(225,72,'field_552c4677ca57d','a:13:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_552c4677ca57d\";s:5:\"label\";s:11:\"English Bio\";s:4:\"name\"