ba3d9'),(843,168,'english-content',''),(844,168,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(845,167,'_wp_trash_meta_status','draft'),(846,167,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1435175368'),(848,96,'_wp_old_slug','espectometria-de-massa'),(849,173,'_edit_last','1'),(850,173,'_edit_lock','1435177746:1'),(851,173,'_wp_trash_meta_status','draft'),(852,173,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1435177845'),(853,174,'_edit_last','1'),(854,174,'_edit_lock','1435772348:1'),(855,174,'english-title','Liquid Chromatography'),(856,174,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(857,174,'english-content','The FPLC consists of a liquid chromatography system often used to purify, analyze and identify quickly and reliably proteins and peptides. This purification is possible due to the fact that each of the blend components preferably have the different stationary phase interactions (solid porous gel resin) or the mobile phase (fluid motion).\r\n\r\nIn this technique, the mobile phase is an aqueous solution or buffer having its flow rate is controlled by a positive displacement pump typically held constant, while the buffer composition may be varied according to the interest. The stationary phase is composed of a resin beads and binding surface, packed in a cylindrical column of glass known as Liquid Chromatography Column.\r\n\r\nThere is a wide range of columns resins for packaging and depending on sample composition its application may be used in different types of columns that including the FPLC ion exchange chromatography techniques, gel filtration, hydrophobic interaction and affinity.'),(858,174,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(859,176,'_edit_last','1'),(860,176,'_edit_lock','1435600559:1'),(861,176,'english-title','What are the controls needed for an experiment in Flow Cytometry?'),(862,176,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(863,176,'english-content','For experiments in flow cytometry different types of controls are needed whenever an experiment is performed. The basic controls are one negative control and controls with the marking of only one color in each tube. The negative controls are single cells or an isotype control. Controls with targeted single color are used to do the compensation of the overlap in spectrum of the emission of the fluorochrome. Single color controls should have enough signal to be able to adjust the instrument settings.'),(864,176,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(865,176,'section',''),(866,176,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(867,177,'_edit_last','1'),(868,177,'english-title','How can I reduce nonspecific labeling?'),(869,177,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(870,177,'english-content','Nonspecific binding may be due to several reasons.\r\n\r\nIf its reaction contains many antibodies, an increase in the amount of unspecific binding of its negative population will occur. You must perform titrations for each antibody used to determine the optimal concentration.\r\n\r\nNonspecific binding can also be due to the Fc portion of the antibody. Use IgG of the same species as its antibody of interest to block unspecific binding.\r\n\r\nThe direct use of conjugated antibodies can also reduce the amount of nonspecific bindings.\r\n\r\nDead cells do not bind any antibody, thus its inclusion in testing with viability marker such as DAPI, PI or 7-AAD, among others, will allow to exclude the dead cell population of the analysis. One should make sure that the marker of viability is compatible with other fluorochromes of your sample. Furthermore, the cells cannot be fixed when using a viability marker as this will make them permeable to the marker and all the cells will appear dead.'),(871,177,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(872,177,'section',''),(873,177,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(874,177,'_edit_lock','1435600598:1'),(875,178,'_edit_last','1'),(876,178,'_edit_lock','1435601543:1'),(877,178,'english-title','How often is data removed from the computer?'),(878,178,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(879,178,'english-content','In order to keep the LaCTAD equipment working properly, data must removed from their computer hard drive regularly.\r\n\r\nEach user has a directory on hard drive for temporary archive and should provide the copy of the files. THE DEADLINE FOR COPY is 30 DAYS. After this period, the files will be deleted without notice.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(880,178,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(881,178,'section','a:1:{i:0;s:2:\"26\";}'),(882,178,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(883,179,'_edit_last','1'),(884,179,'english-title','What types of samples can be tested in Confocal microscope?'),(885,179,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(886,179,'english-content','Samples for analysis can be fixed on slides, tissue sections, cell cultures or living organisms, and can be seen by immunofluorescence labeling with different fluorochromes. The techniques should be appropriate to the type of sample and procedure.'),(887,179,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(888,179,'section',''),(889,179,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(890,179,'_edit_lock','1435601579:1'),(891,180,'_edit_last','1'),(892,180,'_edit_lock','1435601678:1'),(893,180,'english-title','I need protocols for sample preparation. Where can I get them?'),(894,180,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(895,180,'english-content','The LaCTAD provides some basic protocols for the preparation of some specific types of analysis, but it is advisable to follow the instructions of the manufacturer of the reagents you will use.'),(896,180,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(897,180,'section',''),(898,180,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(899,181,'_edit_last','1'),(900,181,'_edit_lock','1435601673:1'),(901,181,'english-title','What are the controls needed for an experiment of Confocal Microscopy?'),(902,181,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(903,181,'english-content','For experiments in Confocal Microscopy different types of controls are needed whenever an experiment is performed. The basic controls consist of one regular slide or without stimulus, two negative control reaction slides (without the incubation of the primary antibody) and when necessary, one positive control slide.'),(904,181,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(905,181,'section',''),(906,181,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(907,180,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(908,180,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1435601825'),(909,182,'_edit_last','1'),(910,182,'_edit_lock','1435602852:1'),(911,182,'english-title','What types of samples can be tested at Bio-plex?'),(912,182,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(913,182,'english-content','The main materials used in the Multiplex Immunoassay (Bio-plex) are serum, plasma and cell culture supernatant. However, besides these ones, adipose tissue interstitial fluid, cerebral fluid, synovial fluid, urine, cell lysate, tissue of the central nervous system, spleen, colon, lung, and liver can be used, among others.'),(914,182,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(915,182,'section',''),(916,182,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(917,183,'_edit_last','1'),(918,183,'_edit_lock','1435606929:1'),(919,183,'external_link','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9FYSo8aqcmg'),(920,183,'_external_link','field_5568c3222a938'),(921,183,'date_published','2013-03-19'),(922,183,'_date_published','field_5568c847fe19b'),(923,184,'_wp_attached_file','2015/06/band.png'),(924,184,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:2000;s:6:\"height\";i:1600;s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"2015/06/band.png\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(925,183,'_thumbnail_id','184'),(926,84,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(927,84,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1435608157'),(928,162,'field_5594254a16e63','a:14:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_5594254a16e63\";s:5:\"label\";s:10:\"iframe url\";s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"iframe_url\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"prepend\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"append\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:4:\"html\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(930,162,'rule','a:5:{s:5:\"param\";s:9:\"post_type\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:8:\"services\";s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;s:8:\"group_no\";i:0;}'),(931,95,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1JH_20qdqOQ6roz0jtLCYwa96_RgkoFpgMtr7g98Ev6c/viewform?embedded=true'),(932,95,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(933,93,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1VAdurk70OMGD6KTQjCf3Cl5RtC2Quy3IfbrOqwhIk48/viewform?embedded=true'),(934,93,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(935,26,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1T6YlKGKX9SuWChfHXFkzns82VFgrBG5bLIArjEo7lKM/viewform?embedded=true'),(936,26,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(937,47,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/147GUG3QzFnZ5Ag8wxO2dRhjITXUMuubjAbXZRwU9kTI/viewform?embedded=true'),(938,47,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(939,50,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1T8l1Fn-6CxsiK4HVfep_axc2Zbmo9w6ss8kTmX8gfNo/viewform?embedded=true'),(940,50,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(941,138,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(942,138,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(943,137,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(944,137,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(945,136,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(946,136,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(947,135,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(948,135,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(949,134,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(950,134,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(951,133,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(952,133,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(953,132,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(954,132,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63'),(955,131,'iframe_url','https://docs.google.com/forms/d/11OEGmL-aEIY8UfZDcwAlPp6uZBjwB_jJa7Z6M_LGeZM/viewform?embedded=true'),(956,131,'_iframe_url','field_5594254a16e63');
